## Phase 3: User Story 1 - Load CSV and View Image Labels (Priority: P1) 🎯 MVP

**Goal**: Enable users to open a CSV file, view the first row's data with column labels, and display the associated image

**Independent Test**: Open a CSV file with headers and IMG_PATH column, verify first row displays with correct image loaded from relative path

### Implementation for User Story 1

- [x] T022 [P] [US1] Implement open_csv Tauri command in src-tauri/src/commands.rs: accept file path, build offset index, detect delimiter, extract headers, return CsvMetadata
- [x] T023 [P] [US1] Implement get_row Tauri command in src-tauri/src/commands.rs: accept row index, seek to offset, parse fields, return RowData
- [x] T024 [P] [US1] Implement get_csv_stats Tauri command in src-tauri/src/commands.rs returning current CsvMetadata from state
- [x] T025 [US1] Register all Tauri commands in src-tauri/src/main.rs: open_csv, get_row, get_csv_stats
- [x] T026 [P] [US1] Create file dialog integration in src/main.ts using @tauri-apps/plugin-dialog to open CSV file
- [x] T027 [P] [US1] Create row editor form component in src/editor.ts: dynamically generate form inputs from headers, populate with field values
- [x] T028 [P] [US1] Create image preview component in src/image-preview.ts: detect IMG_PATH column (case-insensitive), use convertFileSrc to create asset URL, display image with loading state
- [x] T029 [P] [US1] Create HTML layout in src/index.html with two-column layout: image preview area (left) and row editor form (right)
- [x] T030 [P] [US1] Create CSS styling in src/style.css for responsive layout with image preview and form side-by-side
- [x] T031 [US1] Implement CSV open workflow in src/main.ts: file dialog → open_csv command → render form with first row → load image
- [x] T032 [US1] Add error handling for missing images: display placeholder with expected path when IMG_PATH points to non-existent file
- [x] T033 [US1] Add error handling for CSV parsing errors: display user-friendly message with retry option
- [x] T034 [US1] Add status bar in src/index.html displaying current file path, row count, and detected delimiter

**Checkpoint**: At this point, User Story 1 should be fully functional - users can open CSV, view first row with image

