## Phase 4: User Story 2 - Toggle Class Values (Priority: P2)

**Goal**: Enable users to quickly change class labels by toggling between existing values without typing

**Independent Test**: Open a CSV with class columns (name contains "CLASS"), verify toggle controls appear, verify clicking cycles through all unique values for that column

### Implementation for User Story 2

- [ ] T035 [P] [US2] Implement class column detection in src-tauri/src/csv_engine.rs: identify columns with "CLASS" in name (case-insensitive), store indices in CsvState
- [ ] T036 [P] [US2] Implement unique value extraction in src-tauri/src/csv_engine.rs: scan entire column to collect unique values, return as Vec<String>
- [ ] T037 [P] [US2] Implement get_class_columns Tauri command in src-tauri/src/commands.rs returning Map<column_index, Vec<unique_values>>
- [ ] T038 [US2] Register get_class_columns command in src-tauri/src/main.rs
- [ ] T039 [P] [US2] Create toggle UI component in src/editor.ts: replace text input with toggle button for class columns, display current value with click-to-cycle behavior
- [ ] T040 [P] [US2] Implement class value cycling logic in src/editor.ts: on click, find next value in unique values list, wrap to first when reaching end
- [ ] T041 [US2] Integrate class column detection into row editor form generation in src/editor.ts: check if column is class column, render toggle component instead of text input
- [ ] T042 [US2] Add visual distinction for class columns in src/style.css: different background color or icon to indicate toggleable field
- [ ] T043 [US2] Implement unsaved changes tracking in src/editor.ts: set flag when any field changes, prompt user before navigation
- [ ] T044 [US2] Add save/discard prompt dialog when navigating away from modified row in src/editor.ts

**Checkpoint**: At this point, User Stories 1 AND 2 should both work - users can toggle class values efficiently

