## Phase 6: User Story 4 - Edit Non-Class Text Fields (Priority: P4)

**Goal**: Enable users to edit text in non-class columns (notes, descriptions, metadata)

**Independent Test**: Edit a non-class text column, save changes, verify CSV file updated correctly

### Implementation for User Story 4

- [ ] T052 [P] [US4] Implement save_row Tauri command in src-tauri/src/commands.rs: accept row_index and fields Vec<String>, write row using csv_engine, update offsets, return success/error
- [ ] T053 [US4] Register save_row command in src-tauri/src/main.rs
- [ ] T054 [P] [US4] Create text input components in src/editor.ts for non-class columns: free-form text input with proper handling of empty values
- [ ] T055 [P] [US4] Implement save button in src/index.html with keyboard shortcut (Ctrl+S)
- [ ] T056 [US4] Implement save workflow in src/editor.ts: collect all field values (class and text), call save_row command, handle success/error, clear unsaved changes flag
- [ ] T057 [US4] Add retry logic in src/editor.ts for save failures: detect permission errors, disk space errors, file modification conflicts
- [ ] T058 [US4] Add "Save As" option in src/editor.ts when save fails due to permissions: allow user to save to different location
- [ ] T059 [US4] Implement undo/redo for current row in src/editor.ts: store field history, Ctrl+Z/Ctrl+Y shortcuts, only active before save
- [ ] T060 [US4] Add visual indication of unsaved changes in src/editor.ts: asterisk in title bar, highlighted save button

**Checkpoint**: Users can now edit both class and non-class fields with robust save functionality

