## Dependencies & Execution Order

### Phase Dependencies

- **Setup (Phase 1)**: No dependencies - can start immediately
- **Foundational (Phase 2)**: Depends on Setup completion - BLOCKS all user stories
- **User Stories (Phase 3-7)**: All depend on Foundational phase completion
  - User stories can proceed in parallel (if multiple developers) after foundation is complete
  - Or sequentially in priority order (P1 → P2 → P3 → P4 → P5) for single developer
- **Polish (Phase 8)**: Depends on desired user stories being complete (minimally US1-US4)

### User Story Dependencies

- **User Story 1 (P1)**: Can start after Foundational (Phase 2) - No dependencies on other stories - THIS IS THE MVP
- **User Story 2 (P2)**: Can start after Foundational (Phase 2) - Extends US1 by adding toggle controls but US1 must be complete for context
- **User Story 3 (P3)**: Depends on User Story 2 (adds new values to existing toggle system)
- **User Story 4 (P4)**: Can start after Foundational (Phase 2) - Independent of US2/US3 (text editing orthogonal to class toggles)
- **User Story 5 (P5)**: Can start after User Story 1 (enhances navigation introduced in US1)

### Within Each User Story

- Rust backend tasks before frontend tasks (commands must exist before frontend can invoke them)
- Core components before integration tasks
- UI components can be built in parallel with backend commands ([P] marked)
- Story complete before moving to next priority

### Parallel Opportunities

- All Setup tasks (T002-T006) can run in parallel after T001
- All Foundational Rust tasks (T007-T011) can run in parallel
- All Foundational test tasks (T015-T021) can run in parallel after implementation
- Within each user story:
  - Backend commands ([P]) can be built in parallel with frontend components ([P])
  - Multiple UI components within the same story can be built in parallel
- User Stories 2 and 4 can be developed in parallel by different developers (after US1 complete)

---

## Parallel Example: User Story 1

```bash
# Backend and frontend can be built in parallel:
Parallel Group 1:
  Task T022: Implement open_csv Tauri command
  Task T023: Implement get_row Tauri command
  Task T024: Implement get_csv_stats Tauri command
  Task T027: Create row editor form component
  Task T028: Create image preview component
  Task T029: Create HTML layout
  Task T030: Create CSS styling

# After parallel group completes, integration tasks:
Sequential:
  Task T025: Register Tauri commands
  Task T031: Implement CSV open workflow
  Task T032-T034: Error handling and status bar
```

